    },
    {
      "id": "d0753d89243d192b3693de5c5a34a166673e22ff",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 419,
        "name": "Frank Zago",
        "email": "fzago@cray.com",
        "username": "fzago.cray"
      },
      "date": "2017-08-25 16:12:37.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI think this changes nothing. The automake manual says:\n\nIf _DEPENDENCIES is not supplied, it is computed by Automake. The automatically-assigned value is the contents of _LDADD or _LIBADD, with most configure substitutions, -l, -L, -dlopen and -dlpreopen options removed. The configure substitutions that are left in are only ‘$(LIBOBJS)’ and ‘$(ALLOCA)’; these are left because it is known that they will not cause an invalid value for _DEPENDENCIES to be generated.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "d2f47585d8c47e3c84d69181833d434ce8a29c7e",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 125,
        "name": "James Simmons",
        "email": "jsimmons@infradead.org",
        "username": "jsimmons"
      },
      "date": "2017-08-25 16:39:50.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nYeah I found that out this morning. Currently I'm testing to see if statmany is the only problem. BTW I saw some thing about debian based systems mangling rpath. Do you know anything about rpath and if that might be the cause?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "5d8ba6073ee61bd3fbc3751de1eb9135b5b14f2c",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 419,
        "name": "Frank Zago",
        "email": "fzago@cray.com",
        "username": "fzago.cray"
      },
      "date": "2017-08-25 16:50:56.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Do you know anything about rpath and\n > if that might be the cause?\n\nNo idea. I've been looking at building as well. I ran lintian and it reports a bunch of errors and warnings. There's probably some updates to do to these debian files.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
